<img width="750" height="422" class="wp-image-1573618" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire.jpg" alt="Katsina House Assembly" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire.jpg?width=750&amp;auto_optimize=medium 750w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-300x169.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-58x33.jpg?width=58&amp;auto_optimize=medium 58w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-260x146.jpg?width=260&amp;auto_optimize=medium 260w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Fire-200x113.jpg?width=200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 200w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /> An early morning fire razed 11 shops at the Alamu Market in Ilorin, Ilorin West Local Government area of Kwara on Monday. The Kwara Fire Service confirmed the incident in a statement issued by its Head of Media and Publicity, Mr Hassan Adekunle, in Ilorin. “A passerby on motorcycle was the one who noticed the inferno and alerted the state fire service. “Firemen did everything possible and immediately stopped the spread of fire to other shops and subsequently put it out,” Adekunle said. The spokesperson stated that the fire was suspected to be caused by an electric power surge. He advised the general public, especially traders, to always be safety conscious. (NAN)   By Marie-Therese NanlongA fire outbreak from a petrol-laden tanker that fell at the Polo roundabout in Jos, Plateau State has left one person dead while property worth millions of naira were destroyed.Among the property destroyed are parts of the Veterinary Teaching Hospital of the University of Jos, the Jos Metropolitan… In "News" PCN seals 520 shops in Kwara over unethical practices In "News" Stored petrol aided spread of fire at Bodija Market- Fire Service In "News"